OL,3,C'I was at death's door': How a
OL,4,Cshoplifter broke a 20-year cycle of
OL,5,Ccrime
OL,7,F"A by-product from addiction is
OL,8,Fprolific shoplifting," he said. "(You
OL,9,Fare) not bothered about the
OL,10,Fconsequences because addiction is that
OL,11,Fstrong and powerful."
OL,13,FDanny initially relied on friends and
OL,14,Ffamily to pay for his habit, but says
OL,15,Fhe eventually "burnt bridges" and the
OL,16,Fseverity of his lifestyle left him at
OL,17,F"death's door".
