OL,3,C'I was at death's door': How a
OL,4,Cshoplifter broke a 20-year cycle of
OL,5,Ccrime
OL,7,FHe says the job has given him growth
OL,8,Fand ambition once more, saying that
OL,9,Fdetox was the key to exiting the world
OL,10,Fof shoplifting and crime.
OL,12,F"If I can do it - I was a hopeless
OL,13,Falcoholic, hopeless addict - anyone
OL,14,Fcan," he said.
OL,16,FDanny is now focused on making amends
OL,17,Ffor his past. As well as working at
OL,18,FThe Well, he gives to charity and
OL,19,Fvolunteers with a church group in his
OL,20,Ffree time.
